text: Céleste Lett Céleste Lett (born May 7, 1951 in Sarreguemines, Moselle) is a member of the National Assembly of France. He represents the Moselle department, and is a member of the Union for a Popular Movement. He has three sons: Jean-Francois, Philippe, and Alexandre. ==References== Category:1951 births Category:Living people Category:People from Sarreguemines Category:Union for a Popular Movement politicians Category:Deputies of the 12th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:Deputies of the 13th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:Deputies of the 14th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic
